=\"Residential Property Tribunal forms\">application form.</a></p>\n\n<p>The forms are listed under the headings:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>&lsquo;Housing Act appeals and applications&rsquo;</li>\n  <li>‘Right to Buy appeals’</li>\n  <li>‘Park homes’</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Send the form to your <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.justice.gov.uk/global/contacts/hmcts/tribunals/residential-property.htm\" title=\"Residential Property Tribunal contacts\">local rent assessment panel.</a></p>\n\n<h2>Cost of appealing to the tribunal</h2>\n\n<p>You may have to pay a £150 fee for some cases. The application form will tell you if you have to pay a fee.</p>\n\n<p>You can pay by postal order or cheque (made payable to &lsquo;HM Courts &amp; Tribunals Service&rsquo;).</p>\n\n<h2>Help paying costs</h2>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re on benefits, like Income Support, you can ask for help with your fees, using the form below:</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.justice.gov.uk/downloads/global/forms/tribunals/residential-property/rpt2-waiver-fees.doc\" title=\"Download 'Application for reduction or waiver of fees' (DOC, 266KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Application for reduction or waiver of fees’ (DOC, 266KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Get help and advice</h2>\n\n<p>You can get help and advice from your local Citizens Advice Bureau or the Residential Property Tribunal Service:</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Citizens Advice</strong>  </p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.citizensadvice.org.uk/index/getadvice.htm\" title=\"Citizens Advice\" rel=\"external\">Citizens Advice</a><br />\n0844 411 1444 (England)<br />\n0844 477 2020 (Wales)</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Residential Property Tribunal Service</strong>  </p>\n\n<p>0845 600 3178</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>What happens after you send your appeal</h2>\n\n<p>The tribunal may ask you for permission to inspect the property or park home.</p>\n\n<p>You may have to go to a hearing with the council or site owner.</p>\n\n<p>If there isn&rsquo;t a hearing, the tribunal will ask you to send written evidence.</p>\n\n<p>The tribunal will send you a letter giving its decision, usually shortly after any hearing.</p>\n\n<h2>If you disagree with the tribunal&rsquo;s decision</h2>\n\n<p>You may be able to appeal against the decision to a higher tribunal, called the Upper Tribunal (Lands Chamber).</p>\n\n<p>To do this, you have to ask the Residential Property Tribunal for permission to appeal, using the form below:</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.justice.gov.uk/downloads/global/forms/tribunals/residential-property/rpt-permission-jun-11.doc\" title=\"Download 'Application to the Residential Property Tribunal for permission to appeal a decision to the Upper Tribunal (Lands Chamber)' (DOC, 123KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Application to the Residential Property Tribunal for permission to appeal a decision to the Upper Tribunal (Lands Chamber)’ (DOC, 123KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You must send this form to your local rent assessment panel within 21 days of getting its decision.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Find out more about appealing to the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.justice.gov.uk/guidance/courts-and-tribunals/tribunals/lands/index.htm\" title=\"Lands Tribunal guidance\">Upper Tribunal (Lands Chamber).</a></p>\n"}]},"updated_at":"2012-10-22T15:18:30+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Courts, sentencing and tribunals","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/justice%2Fcourts-sentencing-tribunals.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Attending courts, paying fines, appealing a sentence and tribunals","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=justice%2Fcourts-sentencing-tribunals","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/justice/courts-sentencing-tribunals"},"parent":{"title":"Crime, justice and the law","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/justice.json",