 years. These landlords include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>housing associations</li>\n  <li>councils</li>\n  <li>the armed services</li>\n  <li>NHS trusts and foundation trusts</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Eligible properties</h2>\n\n<p>Your property must either have been:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>built or bought by a housing association after 1 April 1997</li>\n  <li>transferred from a local council to a housing association after 1 April 1997</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Your landlord must be registered with the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.homesandcommunities.co.uk/\" title=\"Homes and Communities Agency\">Homes and Communities Agency.</a></p>\n\n<p>The home you want to buy must also be:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a self-contained property</li>\n  <li>your only or main home</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Joint applications</h2>\n\n<p>You can make a joint application with:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>someone who shares your tenancy</li>\n  <li>up to 3 family members who&rsquo;ve lived with you for the past 12 months (even if they don’t share your tenancy)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Who doesn&rsquo;t qualify</h2>\n\n<p>You can’t use Right to Acquire if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re being made <a href=\"/bankruptcy/overview\" title=\"Bankruptcy\">bankrupt</a></li>\n  <li>a court has <a href=\"/council-housing-association-evictions/overview\" title=\"Council and housing association evictions\">ordered you to leave your home</a></li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re a council tenant – you may be able to use <a href=\"/right-to-buy-buying-your-council-home/overview\" title=\"Right to buy: buying your council home\">Right to Buy</a> instead</li>\n</ul>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/right-to-acquire-buying-housing-association-home/discounts","slug":"discounts","order":2,"title":"Discounts","body":"<p>You can get a discount of between £9,000 and £16,000 on the price of your property. </p>\n\n<p>The amount of discount you&rsquo;ll get depends on where you live in the UK.</p>\n\n<p>Your landlord will tell you what discount you&rsquo;ll get 